And we'd be waiting
in the car for you

497
00:27:07,592 --> 00:27:10,083
and we'd see you
come down the ramp.

498
00:27:10,128 --> 00:27:13,723
We got real excited
every time we saw you.

499
00:27:13,765 --> 00:27:16,256
I was there 33½ years.

500
00:27:16,301 --> 00:27:17,960
33½ years?

501
00:27:18,403 --> 00:27:21,201
What's your best memory here,
being here, working here?

502
00:27:21,239 --> 00:27:24,402
My best memory?
I think the people.

503
00:27:24,442 --> 00:27:26,433
They were a really good bunch.

504
00:27:26,477 --> 00:27:29,344
- You liked the crowd you worked with?
- Yeah.

505
00:27:29,380 --> 00:27:32,645
A good place to work. I enjoyed it.

506
00:27:32,684 --> 00:27:35,551
But I'm sorry to see it go.

507
00:27:43,161 --> 00:27:45,891
Shortly before Christmas 2008,

508
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:49,058
Republic Windows & Doors
in Chicago, Illinois,

509
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:52,331
abruptly fired
its entire unionized workforce

510
00:27:52,370 --> 00:27:55,430
of over 250 people.

511
00:27:55,473 --> 00:27:58,931
They were given
only 3 days' notice.

512
00:27:58,977 --> 00:28:01,036
Bank of America
would no longer provide

513
00:28:01,079 --> 00:28:03,274
a line of credit to the company,

514
00:28:03,314 --> 00:28:07,410
and so the workers were not paid
the money owed to them.

515
00:28:07,452 --> 00:28:10,250
My life revolves around this job.

516
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:14,452
I live according to my obligation
to my job, you know?

517
00:28:14,492 --> 00:28:18,553
And it's not just me,
it's all of the workers here.

518
00:28:18,596 --> 00:28:21,394
We go above and beyond

519
00:28:21,432 --> 00:28:24,026
the call of duty for Republic.

520
00:28:24,068 --> 00:28:26,798
And at the end,

521
00:28:26,838 --> 00:28:29,671
Republic cares nothing for us.

522
00:28:31,509 --> 00:28:34,478
We found out that they're gonna
shut the plant on Tuesday.

523
00:28:34,512 --> 00:28:37,743
We don't deserve what
they're doing to us, you know?

524
00:28:37,782 --> 00:28:41,081
It really hurts because,
like I said,

525
00:28:41,119 --> 00:28:43,087
this is my second family.

526
00:28:43,121 --> 00:28:45,715
So it was-- it really hurts.
It really hurts.

527
00:28:45,757 --> 00:28:49,659
I'm gonna miss
all of them, you know?

528
00:28:49,694 --> 00:28:52,663
I'm gonna miss them
and I don't think

529
00:28:52,697 --> 00:28:55,029
anybody on this planet

530
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:58,297
deserves what they've done to us.

531
00:29:05,777 --> 00:29:07,836
Scenes like this
were being repeated

532
00:29:07,879 --> 00:29:11,940
all over the country,
and no one seemed to mind.

